    <sec id="minf202000081-sec-0006">
      <label>2.4</label>
      <title>Computing Time</title>
      <p>All experiments have been carried out on a Dell PowerEdge R940 (Intel Xeon Gold 5220). <sc>sensaas</sc> is running using the Debian version 5.3.15‐1 of Linux. The processing time for molecules used in present tests takes between 3 to 25 seconds per run (Figure <xref rid="minf202000081-fig-0004" ref-type="fig">4</xref>). Computation times of 25 seconds occur when a molecule is aligned on a shifted version of itself, for example in self‐matching tests. However, aligning a molecule on itself is a rare and specific experiment, per se. In our study, we only used it as a control. No optimization of the code was carried out so far but an optimization of the point cloud preprocessing and the use of Python threads over voxel size could bring a substantial improvement in computation times.
</p>
